      "id": "fc8426ef9ad5760e",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "fc8426ef9ad5760e",
        "text": "Tourism today is a profile-building activity. Travel destinations—and almost every place in the world has become a travel destination by now—provide resources for a profile-based identity, or “profilicity.”1 Tourists make use of these resources. They generate identity surplus value out of the profile value supplied by the tourism industry. In tourism, concrete profileidentity work consists in taking and posting photos. The taking and posting of images increases the profile value not only of the tourist but of the destination as well. All participants can experience this creation of value as enjoyable. Apparently our middleaged European friend did not yet understand the joy of tourism under conditions of profilicity."
